					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1552358&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610158254" alt="HammerMaiden" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1552358)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;" >HammerMaiden</a></span> <span class="odate time_1389621228 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Jan 2014 13:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1934775">
									

<p>Repetative is good, in small doses and spread out over longer periods of time. Honestly, because of the similarity in theme and content, I considered that this might be the next entry in a longer &quot;series&quot; of the SCP Technical documents.</p>
<p>This one is particularly interesting in that it tells a story that was entertaining enough, well written enough, and made enough sense in universe for me to up-vote it before finding the pattern-screamer material underneath it. I will say, however, that the pattern-screamer story is a bit weaker in this one than the last, and I wish there was more to it. Regardless, if it already has value before knowing that, adding the extra material doesn't take anything away.</p>
<p>So +1 from me. Cryogen, if you do plan on making this a series, I would like to see something deeper and stranger out of the information beings you're depicting. So far it feels like something is absent from them, I know not what.</p>

							</div>

								
					
